		<div class="main-content">
			<div class="content-row bg--yellow" id="about">
				<div class="content-row-header row d-block no-gutters py-3">
					<div class="container-fluid">
						<div class="d-flex py-1 border-y--dk-green">
							<div class="col text-left text--green f--reg-sm">gardener's delight</div>
							<div class="col text-right text--green f--reg-sm">visual satisfaction</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="content-row-body row d-block no-gutters">
					<div class="container-fluid">
						<div class="d-lg-flex py-4 align-items-center">
							<div class="content-row-text col-lg-7 px-md-5">
								<h2 class="text--green f--mobile"><span class="">Naturalistic</span><br/><em class="text--sm">and</em> wild.</h2>
								<p class="text--green d-block">Your plants and flowers should make you smile. Like the feeling of dipping your toes into the creek on a hot summer day. When the dandelion blown into the wind flies back and lands on your cheek. These are the simple pleasures that living, growing, blooming beauties offer us even in urban environments.<br><br/><a class="text--green" href="https://www.instagram.com/maidencreekco/" target="_blank">Maidencreek Co.</a> is about increasing those moments on a regular basis through arrangements, bouquets, container gardens and window boxes. We focus on seasonal varieties and using more organic, native and local sources when possible.</p>
